1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,869
Looking for your next executive role?

2
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:04,177
That is not the real problem.

3
00:00:04,577 --> 00:00:05,657
The roles are everywhere.

4
00:00:05,978 --> 00:00:09,595
LinkedIn. Job boards. Recruiters. Company sites.

5
00:00:10,374 --> 00:00:12,290
But the truth about a career decision lives somewhere else.

6
00:00:12,474 --> 00:00:21,651
In a CV version. A saved link. An interview note. A salary file.
A conversation you meant to revisit.

7
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:26,090
More access created more fragments. Not more clarity.

8
00:00:27,048 --> 00:00:29,423
Because the problem is not a shortage of jobs.

9
00:00:29,955 --> 00:00:31,751
It is a shortage of intelligence.

10
00:00:32,743 --> 00:00:35,817
What if every opportunity arrived with context?

11
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:44,165
Why it fits. Why it may not. What is confirmed. What is unknown.
What deserves your attention next.

12
00:00:45,024 --> 00:00:47,036
That is Executive Intelligence.

13
00:00:47,948 --> 00:00:49,712
Most platforms help people apply.

14
00:00:50,307 --> 00:00:52,612
ORENDALIS helps executives decide.

15
00:00:53,598 --> 00:00:55,685
The executive hiring process is broken.

16
00:00:56,152 --> 00:00:57,810
It is time to expect better.
